/**
 * CURRICULUM TEMPLATE
 * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * Copy this file when adding a new language. Replace every [PLACEHOLDER] with
 * real content. Delete courses that are not yet ready — start with first_words
 * and songs, then expand.
 *
 * ALL IDs ARE GLOBALLY UNIQUE. Each language uses its two-letter abbreviation
 * as a prefix so IDs are self-documenting and each language counts from 1.
 *
 *   ID type        Format              Example
 *   ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 *   Course         {lang}-course-N     iz-course-1
 *   Lesson         {lang}-lesson-N     iz-lesson-1
 *   Segment        {lang}-tN-M         iz-t1-1  (lesson N, segment M)
 *   Dictionary     d-{lang}-N          d-iz-1
 *   Proverb        pv-{lang}-N         pv-iz-1
 *   Cultural       cult-{lang}-N       cult-iz-1
 *   Sentence       s-{lang}-N          s-iz-1
 *
 * Two-letter abbreviations: iz yo ig ha sw am ak wo ae so ba tz kr ew
 * Each language starts all counters at 1.
 *
 * AFTER CREATING THIS FILE:
 *   1. Add course entries to  lib/data/courses.ts
 *   2. Register the lesson array in  lib/data/lessons/index.ts  (ALL_LESSONS)
 *   3. Create a dictionary file  lib/data/[lang].ts  and register it in
 *      lib/data/index.ts  (DICTIONARY_REGISTRY)
 *   4. Add to  lib/data/languages.ts + LANGUAGES_WITH_CONTENT
 *   5. Optionally: proverbs/, cultural/, sentences/
 *
 * POSTING DIRECTLY TO THE DATABASE (preferred going forward):
 *   Skip the seed file entirely and insert via the API or a one-off script.
 *
 *   Option A — Admin API (recommended):
 *     POST /api/admin/lessons  { lessons: [...] }
 *     POST /api/admin/courses  { courses: [...] }
 *   Content of `lessons` = the lesson arrays below (JSON-serialised).
 *
 *   Option B — Server seed script (server/src/seed/):
 *     import { NEWLANG_FIRST_WORDS_LESSONS } from "mobile/lib/data/lessons/[lang].ts";
 *     await db.insert(lessons).values(NEWLANG_FIRST_WORDS_LESSONS).onConflictDoNothing();
 *   Run with:  npx tsx server/src/seed/[lang].ts
 *
 *   Seed files are still useful for local dev resets; for production, prefer
 *   Option A so content goes live without a redeploy.
 *
 * COURSE ORDER (same sequence for every language):
 *   1. first_words      beginner      greetings, names, identity, family      (11 lessons)
 *   2. sound_script     beginner      phonology, tones, script                ( 6 lessons)
 *   3. numbers_trade    beginner      counting, market, money                 ( 8 lessons)
 *   4. communicative    beginner      dialogues, registers, politeness        (16 lessons)
 *   5. oral_tradition   intermediate  proverbs, folktales, praise poetry      ( 8 lessons)
 *   6. songs            beginner      traditional songs, lullabies            ( 3 songs  )
 *
 * Minimum viable launch: first_words + songs.
 * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 */

